context: Between 1402 and 1405, the expedition led by the Norman noble <b1_0>Jean de Bethencourt and the Poitevine Gadifer de la Salle<b1_0/> conquered the <b2_0>Canarian islands<b2_0/> of Lanzarote, Fuerteventura and El Hierro off the Atlantic coast of <a0_0><a0_1><a0_2>Africa<a0_2/><a0_1/><a0_0/>. Their troops were gathered in Normandy, Gascony and were later reinforced by Castilian colonists.
